  "body": "### Description\n\nFlyway has a `repair` command (see https://flywaydb.org/documentation/command/repair), which has the following uses:\r\n- Remove failed migration entries (only for databases that do NOT support DDL transactions)\r\n- Realign the checksums, descriptions, and types of the applied migrations with the ones of the available migrations\r\n- Mark all missing migrations as deleted\r\n\r\nI really like the Quarkus Flyway `migrate-at-start` option. When using that I don't quite see how I can easily run a `repair` command in production, should that ever be necessary. So I propose that there is something like a `repair-at-start` or `repair-before-migrate` config which can be set to allow for this use case.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
